<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="V" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Vale" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Vale,</orth> low ground (used only in verse): <bibl n="shak. lc 2" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.120" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 2, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.11.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 11, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.176" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 176</bibl>. Metaphorically, a place and state of misery or decline: <cit><quote>his comfort in this earthly v.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.70" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 70</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I am declined into the v. of years,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.266" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 266</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>